# Purchases – Get Purchase Details
# Smoke tests for GET /purchases/{purchase_id}.
#
# Authenticated endpoint. A user can only retrieve their own purchases;
# accessing another user's purchase yields 403 (not 404, to avoid
# information leakage about purchase existence).
#
# Seed data used:
#   alice owns:  aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001 (txn_seed_001, status=pending, Shoply)
#                aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000005 (txn_seed_005, status=confirmed, Shoply)
#   bob owns:    aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003 (txn_seed_003)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8001/api/v1

# Paste a fresh user token here (use the helper login request below).
# This placeholder value is an expired local-dev token from seed data — never a real credential.
@userToken = Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoiYjdlMmMxYTItNGYzYS00ZTJiLTljMWEtOGQyZTNmNGI1YzZkIiwidXNlcl9yb2xlIjoidXNlciIsImV4cCI6MTc3MzA3ODUwMX0.Ca9bXYtSnqUnLrH8tc5s5ns7hsfJ70YipKUFOJ8Ce8Q

### Helper – obtain a fresh user token (alice)
# Returns access_token — paste as "Bearer <token>" into @userToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}

### 200 – Happy path: owner retrieves their own pending purchase
# alice requests her own purchase; full detail object expected.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases/aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 200 – Happy path: owner retrieves their own confirmed purchase
# Verifies the response includes cashback amount and confirmed status.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases/aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000005
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 403 – Sad path: user attempts to view another user's purchase
# alice requests bob's purchase — ownership check fails.
# Expects: 403 FORBIDDEN (not 404, to avoid leaking purchase existence).
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases/aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000003
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 404 – Sad path: purchase does not exist
# All-zero UUID is guaranteed to have no database row.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: {{userToken}}

### 401 – Sad path: missing authentication
# No Authorization header; expects 401 UNAUTHORIZED from the auth middleware.
GET {{baseUrl}}/purchases/aa000001-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
